<br>
Group Friendly spells that do not improve soloing are easy, can't think of anything that would improve a group that would not also apply to raids however.<br>
<br>
Ideas:<br>
<br>
1. Damage Add Debuff-- Every time the creature is struck by a weapon or hit by a spell, extra damage is added to the attack.  &quot;You slash a Mob for 20&quot; &quot;Your blow drives shards of ice into a Mob for 20&quot;.  Might help soloing one mob at a time, but something like this would obviously help melee much more than casters.  I understand that clerics get something similar, but damage is hardly their primary function, nor even their secondary one.<br>
<br>
2. Fast mana regen spell-- This is the one where most think I'm off my rocker.  Based on the idea of harvest, only it's a buff that lasts 30-45 seconds and can refill a mana bar in that time.  Limitations are that if you are aggroed, move, or cast a spell, the buff is instantly gone.  Coding would be difficult to not be abused on raids however, this should not be a new Mod Rod, but something to aid dungeon crawlers so that progress down the hall can actually be made between fights while not limiting the casters to one spell per fight.  Might help soloing in the respect you can do it faster, but would not allow you to solo things you otherwise would not, like KEI does due to it's constant mana regen effect.<br>
<br>
3. and though it's not my idea, I liked it.  Aggressive/Conservative (suggested self only, but I hate self only) buffs.  Aggressive is a stackable with everything damage focus, that costs more mana per nuke.  Conservative is a Damage suppressing, but costs less per nuke. <p><br>
